<HEAD>Hunter Admits Error in Waiting to Report Finding Bones</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BENTONVILLE, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hunter says he was wrong to wait a
day before reporting the discovery of the remains of a woman.
   Wayne T. Grantham, 21, of Rogers was hunting Sept. 16 when he
found the remains of Dana Stidham of Centerton, who disappeared on
July 26. Her death is being investigated as a homicide.
   Grantham said Thursday that he waited not just because he was
late for an afternoon of dove hunting with a friend, but also
because he did not realize the remains were recent.
   ``I knew there were a lot of Civil War relics and Indian relics
in the area, and I thought it might be something like that,'' he
said.
   The bones ``weren't going anywhere,'' he said. ``I'll admit it.
I was wrong.''
   He denied a report by the Benton County sheriff's office that he
had said he waited to report the bones because he didn't want to
disturb the area for hunting. He has not been charged in the case.
