<HEAD>Typhoon Brian Kills 31 People</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A typhoon has killed 31 people and injured 493
others on an island off China's southeast coast, the official news
agency said Thursday.
   Xinhua said Typhoon Brian hit Hainan Island on Monday night and
caused severe flooding and damage to homes, roads and
communications lines. It did not say if the downed lines were the
reason for the delay in announcing the deaths.
   Hainan, south of Hong Kong, became China's newest province last
year and has been marked for rapid economic development. However,
its infrastructure remains weak and farming is still the main
occupation of most residents.
   Hundreds of people died in two typhoons that struck further
north on China's coast earlier this year. Authorities said last
month that nearly 3,000 people died in flooding in China in the
summer alone.
