<FIRST>r a AM-PlaneCrash     10-06 0164</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Plane Crash,0167</SECOND>
<HEAD>Small Plane Crash At Airport Kills Four On Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALM SPRINGS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A single-engine plane crashed short
of the runway at Palm Springs Regional Airport on Thursday evening,
killing all four people on board, an airport official said.
   The Piper Arrow was coming in for a landing in clear weather
when it hit the desert sand at 5:15 p.m., several yards short of
the runway, said airport Director of Aviation Allen Smoot. No one
on the ground was injured.
   ``There was some turbulence,'' said Val Lanese. ``I could see it
was in trouble. The left wing was straight up in the air and it
crashed onto its right wing.''
   The identities of the victims and cause of the crash were not
immediately known. The Federal Aviation Administration and the
Riverside County coroner were investigating.
   Smoot said the crash closed the airport briefly, but no
commercial flights were delayed in this desert resort 100 miles
east of Los Angeles.
</TEXT>
