<HEAD>London Shares End Slightly Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   London shares ended slightly lower on London's
Stock Exchange Friday, but well above their session lows, as the
market rallied on the back of renewed takeover speculation
surrounding Jaguar and Saatchi and Saatchi.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index ended 4.1
points, or 0.2 percent, lower at 2,277.5. At one point it had been
down 31.7 points.
   The market opened sharply weaker in reaction to the British
government action to raise interest rates a full percentage point
to 15 percent on Thursday.
   But buying interest in Jaguar PLC and Saatchi and Saatchi PLC
pushed the market forward. Ford Motor Co. announced it had received
U.S. regulatory clearance to begin buying up to 15 percent of
Jaguar, and advertising giant Saatchi and Saatchi was the subject
of takeover rumors.
   The Financial Times 30-share index fell 8.4 points to close at
1,857.8. The Financial Times 500-share index fell 3.79 points to
close at 1,269.37.
   Volume amounted to a fairly heavy 505.5 million shares Friday,
compared with 491.4 million shares Thursday.
