<SECOND>BC-Soviet Slot Machines,0111</SECOND>
<HEAD>One-Armed Bandit Company Scores Jackpot With Soviets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small Swedish firm has signed a
jackpot deal to sell 25,000 one-armed bandits to the Soviet Union,
the national news agency TT reported Friday.
   The company, Bonik AB, almost went bankrupt after the Swedish
authorities banned the gambling slot machine 10 years ago.
   TT said Bonik was buying existing machines from all over Sweden
and adapting the coin slots for rubles before transporting them by
truck to various towns in the Soviet Union.
   Bonik was to supply the machines over a 10-year period. The
first 250 have already been delivered.
