   The stock market climbed toward new highs today,
responding to the latest evidence of sluggish economic growth.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 11.96 points to
2,785.52 by 2 p.m. on Wall Street.
   Gainers outnumbered losers by about 7 to 6 in nationwide trading
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 775 up, 651 down and
476 unchanged.
