<FIRST>u f AM-OilPrices     10-06 0217</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0228</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oil Futures Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oil futures prices finished mixed Friday in
light, uneventful dealings.
   Crude oil futures traded on the New York Mercantile Exchange
moved lower. The November contract for West Texas Intermediate, the
benchmark grade of U.S. crude which slipped 19 cents on Thursday,
lost another 9 cents to finish at $19.87 per 42-gallon barrel.
Subsequent months also retreated.
   Among petroleum products, gasoline futures contracts traded on
the exchange also fell while home heating oil rose.
   The November contract for unleaded gasoline was down 0.17 cent
to 54.80 cents a gallon. The near-term contract for home heating
oil, which tumbled 1.08 cents a gallon on Thursday, finished up
0.27 cent at 58.18 cents a gallon.
   Trading was very light. ``There's very little happening,'' said
Peter Beutel, an assistant director at Elders Futures Inc.
``Basically people are balancing their books before the weekend.''
   Beutel predicted trading would continue at a slow pace on Monday
since many traders will be out in observance of Yom Kippur.
   Reports that representatives of 12 independent oil-producing
nations would issue a communique on talks held for the past two
days in Kuala Lumpur had little effect on the day's activity in the
pits.
   The communique is scheduled to be issued at 5 a.m. EDT Saturday.
</TEXT>
