<FIRST>r f AM-Vitro-Anchor     10-06 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Vitro-Anchor,0134</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mexican Glass Maker Extends Bid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vitro, S.A. announced Friday that it again
was extending its tender offer for Tampa's Anchor Glass Container
Corp., this time until Oct. 13.
   The Mexican glassmaker said so far 8,944,976 shares of Anchor's
common stock have been tendered to THR Corp., a subsidary of Vitro.
These shares, plus 1,430,300 shares owned by THR and its
affiliates, represent about 75 percent of Anchor's outstanding
common shares.
   Vitro said it has entered into a confidentiality agreement with
Anchor under which the Tampa glassmaker has agreed to provide Vitro
the same confidential information provided to third parties.
   Vitro made an unsolicited $20-a-share offer for Anchor Aug. 9
and several times has extended its offer a week at a time.
</TEXT>
