<TEXT>
   Deregulation of the airline industry has led
to domination of domestic air travel by a few companies, two
Republican senators said Friday in introducing legislation they say
would increase competition.
   Sens. John C. Danforth, R-Mo., and John McCain, R-Ariz., said
that deregulation has failed to benefit the traveling public,
despite an early flurry of competition, but that their bill is not
a return to regulation.
   Among the bill's provisions is a prohibition against airlines
owning computerized reservation services.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. has received U.S. regulatory
clearance to buy up to 15 percent of Jaguar PLC.
   Ford received early clearance from the Federal Trade Commission,
which must approve major share acquisitions under the
Hart-Scott-Rodino Act, a Ford U.K. spokesman said Friday.
   Ford announced Sept. 19 that it wanted to buy up to 15 percent
of Jaguar, and left open the option of making a full bid for the
British luxury automaker.
</TEXT>
