<TEXT>
   A small Swedish company has signed a
jackpot deal to sell 25,000 one-armed bandits to the Soviet Union,
the Swedish national news agency TT reported.
   TT said Friday that the company, Bonik AB, was buying existing
machines from all over Sweden and adapting the coin slots for
rubles before transporting them by truck to various towns in the
Soviet Union.
   Bonik almost went bankrupt after Swedish authorities banned the
gambling slot machine 10 years ago.
</TEXT>
